The paper focuses on solving the loop-closure detection problem for self-driving vehicles, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. The proposed approach incorporates deep learning-based point cloud description and sequence matching strategies, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions a typical place analysis approach, which involves analyzing the feature space distribution, and a coarse-to-fine strategy, which involves matching at different levels of granularity, both of which are related to natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
